{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-js","path":"/blog/2024-08-13-how-to-add-more-than-one-style-in-react-js/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"excerpt":"Hi Friends üëã, Welcome To aHoisting! To add more than one style in react js, you can use . It will add more than one style in react js. Today, I am going to‚Ä¶","html":"<p>Hi Friends üëã,</p>\n<p>Welcome To aHoisting!</p>\n<p>To add more than one style in react js, you can use <code class=\"language-text\">style={{...baseStyle, ...enhancedStyle}}</code>. It will add more than one style in react js.</p>\n<p>Today, I am going to show you, how to add more than one style in react js.</p>\n<p>Table of contents</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Install and create a new React app.</li>\n<li>Import react component.</li>\n<li>Create a Component.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Let‚Äôs start with the first step.</p>\n<h3>Step 1: Install and create a new React app.</h3>\n<p>First you have to install the React project. You should use <code class=\"language-text\">create-react-app</code> command to create a new React project.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\">npx create<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>react<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>app my<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>app\ncd my<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>app\nnpm start</code></pre></div>\n<h3>Step 2: Import react component.</h3>\n<p>After installing, you have to import your React component.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> React <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'react'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<h3>Step 3: Create a Component.</h3>\n<p>You can use <code class=\"language-text\">style={{...baseStyle, ...enhancedStyle}}</code> to add more than one style in react js.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>h1 style<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token operator\">...</span>baseStyle<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token operator\">...</span>enhancedStyle<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>aHoisting<span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>h1<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<h3>Add more than one style example.</h3>\n<p>The below code is an example of a React. You have to import <code class=\"language-text\">./App.css</code> and set <code class=\"language-text\">style={{...baseStyle, ...enhancedStyle}}</code> to add more than one style in react js.</p>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">App.js</code></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> React <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'react'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> <span class=\"token function-variable function\">App</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">let</span> baseStyle <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token literal-property property\">color</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">'red'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">let</span> enhancedStyle <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token literal-property property\">fontSize</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">'38px'</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>h1 style<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token operator\">...</span>baseStyle<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token operator\">...</span>enhancedStyle<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>aHoisting<span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>h1<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">export</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">default</span> App<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>In the above code example, I have used the <code class=\"language-text\">style={{...baseStyle, ...enhancedStyle}}</code> to add more than one style in react js.</p>\n<p>Check the output of the above code.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 443px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/d8b1699e2103a7c11d5cbe2af9c5466a/23445/more-than-one-style.webp\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-botto